cription": "Area: SIMD (Single Instruction Multiple Data)"}, {"id": 1282665911, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMjgyNjY1OTEx", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-const-generics", "name": "A-const-generics", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: const generics (parameters and arguments)"}, {"id": 1353616418, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMzUzNjE2NDE4", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-intrinsics", "name": "A-intrinsics", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: intrinsics"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 17, "created_at": "2021-05-12T14:19:52Z", "updated_at": "2021-06-09T19:05:33Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "`simd_shuffle` requires its last parameter, the array defining the shuffling, to be a constant:\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/487e27350a16e35f77ca471f368be3da28dac27c/compiler/rustc_codegen_llvm/src/intrinsic.rs#L888\r\n\r\nCurrently (after https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/85110), this is enforced by an ad-hoc hack in `compiler/rustc_mir/src/transform/lower_intrinsics.rs`.\r\n\r\nBut I think it'd be better to instead change the type of `simd_shuffle` to make the shuffle array a const generic parameter. I am not doing this yet since const generic arrays require enabling an `incomplete_feature` which is not great, but once const generic arrays are sufficiently stable we could use them as a more principled way to ensure that `simd_shuffle` is called in the right way.\r\n\r\nCc @rust-lang/project-const-generics ", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/85229/reactions", "total_count": 6, "+1": 6, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/85229/timeline", "performed_via_github_app